                "protocols": [
                    {
                        "comments": [],
                        "name": "Sample collection",
                        "protocolType": {
                            "comments": [],
                            "annotationValue": "Sample collection",
                            "termSource": null,
                            "termAccession": ""
                        },
                        "description": "<p>Testis samples were harvested from both <strong>control</strong> (<strong>CON)</strong> and <strong>non-absorbable antibiotics</strong> (<strong>nABX</strong>)-treated sire males across the 3 breeding timepoints: immediately after <strong>6-week treatment</strong> (11 weeks old mice), <strong>4-week after treatment withdrawal/recovery</strong> (15 weeks old mice) and <strong>8-week after treatment withdrawal/recovery</strong> (19 weeks old mice). Immediately after collection, samples were snap-frozen in liquid nitrogen and stored at -80 \u00b0C.</p>",
                        "uri": "",
                        "version": "",
                        "parameters": [
                            {
                                "comments": [],
                                "parameterName": {
                                    "comments": [],
                                    "annotationValue": "",
                                    "termSource": null,
                                    "termAccession": ""
                                }
                            }
                        ],
                        "components": []
                    },
                    {
                        "comments": [],
                        "name": "Extraction",
                        "protocolType": {
                            "comments": [],
                            "annotationValue": "Extraction",
                            "termSource": null,
                            "termAccession": ""
                        },
                        "description": "<p>Upon retrieval, 300 \u03bcL of ice-cold solvent mixture (acetonitrile:methanol:water, 2:2:1) and two Tungsten Carbide Beads, 3 mm from Qiagen (Hilden, Germany) were added to each testicle sample. Samples were homogenized using Qiagen tissueLyser II at 30% strength for 5 min. The lysed samples were centrifuged at 12,700 RCF at 4 \u00b0C for 10 min. An equal volume (125 \u03bcL) of extraction supernatant was transferred to two Nunc 96-well, V-shape plates and evaporated in the Genevac centrifugal concentrator (Genevac, Ipswich, UK) at 25 \u00b0C for 2 h. Concentrated samples were stored at -80 \u00b0C and resuspended in 20 \u03bcL of same solvent mixture for LC-MS analysis.</p>",
                        "uri": "",
                        "version": "",
                        "parameters": [
                            {
                                "comments": [],
                                "parameterName": {
                                    "comments": [],
                                    "annotationValue": "Post Extraction",
                                    "termSource": null,
                                    "termAccession": ""
                                }
                            },
                            {
                                "comments": [],
                                "parameterName": {
                                    "comments": [],
                                    "annotationValue": "Derivatization",
                                    "termSource": null,
                                    "termAccession": ""
                                }
                            }
                        ],
                        "components": []
                    },
                    {
                        "comments": [],
                        "name": "Chromatography",
                        "protocolType": {
                            "comments": [],
                            "annotationValue": "Chromatography",
                            "termSource": null,
                            "termAccession": ""
                        },
                        "description": "<p>Chromatographic separation was performed using an Agilent InfinityLab Poroshell 120 EC-C18, 3.0 mm x 150 mm, 2.7 \u03bcm column and an Agilent 1290 Infinity II LC system coupled to a 6550 iFunnel qToF mass spectrometer. Column temperature was maintained at 45 \u00b0C with a flowrate of 0.4 mL/min. The following mobile phases were used: mobile phase A: water with 0.1% formic acid and mobile phase B: acetonitrile with 0.1% formic acid. In total 5 mL of sample were injected at 5% mobile phase B, maintained for 0.10 min, followed by a linear gradient to 30% B in 0.5 min, followed by a linear gradient to 95% B in 10 min and maintained at 95% B for 1 min. The column was allowed to re-equilibrate with starting conditions for 3 min before each sample injection protocol description.</p>",
